{
  "meta": {
    "format_version": 2,
    "spec_url": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/workflowpeople/wfp-format/main/SPEC.md",
    "exported_at": "2026-04-11T05:38:55.976Z",
    "workspace": "My Workspace"
  },
  "app_workflows": [
    {
      "workflow_id": "wf-b53a13",
      "name": "Bank Statement GL Categorization",
      "description": "## Purpose\nThis workflow helps you assign general ledger categories to transactions imported from your bank statement. It eliminates manual sorting by organizing raw bank data into the correct accounts for accurate financial reporting.\n\n## When to use\n- After importing a new bank statement into the system\n- When uncategorized transactions are flagging in your account\n- During month-end close to ensure all transactions are properly coded before finalizing books\n\n## Steps\n1. **Categorize Transactions** — Review each imported bank transaction and assign it to the appropriate GL account. The system may suggest categories based on past patterns, which you can accept or override.\n2. **Build Report** — The system compiles all categorized transactions into a structured summary, grouping entries by GL account and calculating totals across the selected date range.\n3. **Download Report** — Export the completed report to your preferred file format for record-keeping, audit purposes, or sharing with your accountant.\n\n## Outputs\n- A categorized transaction ledger mapping each bank entry to a GL account\n- A summary report grouped by account with transaction counts and totals\n- A downloadable file (such as CSV or PDF) ready for external use or filing",
      "type": "automation",
      "nodes": "[{\"node_id\":\"node-9219cb\",\"workflow_id\":\"wf-b53a13\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"label\":\"Start\",\"step_order\":1,\"tool_id\":\"workflow_start\",\"toolConfig\":{},\"toolParameters\":{},\"workflowMgmt\":{\"enabled\":true}},{\"workflow_id\":\"wf-b53a13\",\"node_id\":\"node-ceffc8\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"label\":\"Categorize Transactions\",\"tool_id\":\"ctool-003f28\",\"toolParameters\":{\"bank_statement\":\"{{bank_statement}}\",\"chart_of_accounts\":\"{{chart_of_accounts}}\"},\"step_order\":2},{\"workflow_id\":\"wf-b53a13\",\"node_id\":\"node-fb0938\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"label\":\"Build Report\",\"tool_id\":\"ctool-0a37ea\",\"toolParameters\":{\"categorized_transactions\":\"{{categorized_transactions}}\"},\"step_order\":3},{\"workflow_id\":\"wf-b53a13\",\"node_id\":\"node-5db5a1\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"label\":\"Download Report\",\"tool_id\":\"download_data\",\"toolParameters\":{\"data\":\"{{report_html}}\",\"filename\":\"gl_categorization_report.html\",\"inline\":\"true\"},\"step_order\":4},{\"workflow_id\":\"wf-b53a13\",\"node_id\":\"node-0fc41d\",\"type\":\"end\",\"label\":\"End\",\"tool_id\":\"workflow_end\",\"step_order\":5}]",
      "edges": "[]",
      "created_at": "2026-04-11T05:35:45.400Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-11T05:35:45.734Z",
      "version": 1,
      "snapshot_data": null,
      "builder_chat": null,
      "summary": "Use this workflow to automatically categorize transactions from a bank statement into general ledger accounts and generate a downloadable report. Run it at the end of a period when you need to reconcile bank activity with your GL or prepare records for review."
    }
  ],
  "app_custom_tools": [
    {
      "tool_id": "ctool-003f28",
      "name": "GL Transaction Categorizer",
      "description": "Read bank_statement (columns: date, description, amount, type) and chart_of_accounts (columns: account_code, account_name, category). For each transaction in bank_statement, use api.llm.classify() to assign the most appropriate GL account from chart_of_accounts. Build the classify prompt by listing all available accounts as: 'account_code - account_name (category)' and asking the model to pick the best match for the transaction description and type. The classify call should return a JSON object with fields: account_code, account_name, category, confidence (high/medium/low). After classifying all transactions, build an array of enriched records: { date, description, amount, type, account_code, account_name, category, confidence }. Also compute a summary array grouped by category: { category, account_code, account_name, transaction_count, total_amount } where total_amount is the sum of amounts for that group. Output categorized_transactions as { records: [...], summary: [...], total_credits: number, total_debits: number }.",
      "description_md": "## What it does\nRead bank_statement (columns: date, description, amount, type) and chart_of_accounts (columns: account_code, account_name, category). For each transaction in bank_statement, use api.llm.classify() to assign the most appropriate GL account from chart_of_accounts. Build the classify prompt by listing all available accounts as: 'account_code - account_name (category)' and asking the model to pick the best match for the transaction description and type. The classify call should return a JSON object with fields: account_code, account_name, category, confidence (high/medium/low). After classifying all transactions, build an array of enriched records: { date, description, amount, type, account_code, account_name, category, confidence }. Also compute a summary array grouped by category: { category, account_code, account_name, transaction_count, total_amount } where total_amount is the sum of amounts for that group. Output categorized_transactions as { records: [...], summary: [...], total_credits: number, total_debits: number }.\n\n## Inputs\n- **bank_statement** — {{bank_statement}}\n- **chart_of_accounts** — {{chart_of_accounts}}\n\n## Outputs\n- **categorized_transactions** — { records: array of enriched transactions with GL assignment, summary: array of totals grouped by category, total_credits: number, total_debits: number }",
      "category": "custom_tool",
      "code": "const bankStatement = api.getParameter(\"bank_statement\");\nconst chartOfAccounts = api.getParameter(\"chart_of_accounts\");\n\n// Build the account list string for classification context\nconst accountList = chartOfAccounts.map(a => `${a.account_code} - ${a.account_name} (${a.category})`).join('\\n');\n\n// Classify all transactions\nconst classifyContext = `You are a GL accountant. Given a bank transaction description and type, pick the best matching GL account from the list below. Return a JSON object with fields: account_code, account_name, category, confidence (high/medium/low).\\n\\nAvailable accounts:\\n${accountList}`;\n\nconst classifyResult = await api.llm.classify({\n  data: bankStatement,\n  categories: chartOfAccounts.map(a => `${a.account_code} - ${a.account_name} (${a.category})`),\n  field: \"gl_assignment\",\n  context: classifyContext\n});\n\nconst classifiedRows = classifyResult.data;\n\n// Parse the gl_assignment field and build enriched records\nconst records = classifiedRows.map(row => {\n  let account_code = null;\n  let account_name = null;\n  let category = null;\n  let confidence = \"low\";\n\n  const assignment = row.gl_assignment || \"\";\n\n  // Try to parse as JSON first\n  try {\n    const parsed = JSON.parse(assignment);\n    account_code = parsed.account_code || null;\n    account_name = parsed.account_name || null;\n    category = parsed.category || null;\n    confidence = parsed.confidence || \"low\";\n  } catch (e) {\n    // Try to match against chart of accounts by account_code in the string\n    const matchedAccount = chartOfAccounts.find(a =>\n      assignment.includes(a.account_code)\n    );\n    if (matchedAccount) {\n      account_code = matchedAccount.account_code;\n      account_name = matchedAccount.account_name;\n      category = matchedAccount.category;\n      confidence = \"medium\";\n    } else {\n      // Try matching by account_name\n      const matchedByName = chartOfAccounts.find(a =>\n        assignment.toLowerCase().includes(a.account_name.toLowerCase())\n      );\n      if (matchedByName) {\n        account_code = matchedByName.account_code;\n        account_name = matchedByName.account_name;\n        category = matchedByName.category;\n        confidence = \"low\";\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  return {\n    date: row.date,\n    description: row.description,\n    amount: parseFloat(row.amount) || 0,\n    type: row.type,\n    account_code,\n    account_name,\n    category,\n    confidence\n  };\n});\n\n// Compute summary grouped by category + account\nconst summaryMap = {};\nfor (const rec of records) {\n  const key = `${rec.category}||${rec.account_code}||${rec.account_name}`;\n  if (!summaryMap[key]) {\n    summaryMap[key] = {\n      category: rec.category,\n      account_code: rec.account_code,\n      account_name: rec.account_name,\n      transaction_count: 0,\n      total_amount: 0\n    };\n  }\n  summaryMap[key].transaction_count += 1;\n  summaryMap[key].total_amount += rec.amount;\n}\n\nconst summary = Object.values(summaryMap).map(s => ({\n  ...s,\n  total_amount: Math.round(s.total_amount * 100) / 100\n}));\n\n// Compute totals\nlet total_credits = 0;\nlet total_debits = 0;\nfor (const rec of records) {\n  const amt = rec.amount;\n  const t = (rec.type || \"\").toLowerCase();\n  if (t === \"credit\") {\n    total_credits += amt;\n  } else if (t === \"debit\") {\n    total_debits += amt;\n  } else {\n    // Fallback: positive = credit, negative = debit\n    if (amt >= 0) total_credits += amt;\n    else total_debits += Math.abs(amt);\n  }\n}\ntotal_credits = Math.round(total_credits * 100) / 100;\ntotal_debits = Math.round(total_debits * 100) / 100;\n\n// Set output\napi.setParameter(\"categorized_transactions\", {\n  _meta: { type: \"json_object\" },\n  data: {\n    records,\n    summary,\n    total_credits,\n    total_debits\n  }\n});\n\n// Build summary HTML for display\nconst summaryRows = summary.map(s => `\n  <tr>\n    <td style=\"padding:6px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;\">${s.category || 'Unassigned'}</td>\n    <td style=\"padding:6px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;\">${s.account_code || '-'}</td>\n    <td style=\"padding:6px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;\">${s.account_name || '-'}</td>\n    <td style=\"padding:6px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;text-align:center;\">${s.transaction_count}</td>\n    <td style=\"padding:6px 12px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;text-align:right;\">$${s.total_amount.toFixed(2)}</td>\n  </tr>\n`).join('');\n\nconst confidenceCounts = { high: 0, medium: 0, low: 0 };\nfor (const rec of records) {\n  const c = rec.confidence || \"low\";\n  if (confidenceCounts[c] !== undefined) confidenceCounts[c]++;\n}\n\napi.addMessage({ html: `\n  <div style=\"font-family:sans-serif;max-width:900px;\">\n    <h2 style=\"color:#1e293b;margin-bottom:4px;\">GL Transaction Categorization Complete</h2>\n    <p style=\"color:#64748b;margin-top:0;\">${records.length} transactions categorized across ${summary.length} GL account groups.</p>\n\n    <div style=\"display:flex;gap:16px;margin-bottom:24px;flex-wrap:wrap;\">\n      <div style=\"background:#f0fdf4;border:1px solid #86efac;border-radius:8px;padding:12px 20px;min-width:140px;\">\n        <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#16a34a;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;\">Total Credits</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size:22px;font-weight:700;color:#15803d;\">$${total_credits.toFixed(2)}</div>\n      </div>\n      <div style=\"background:#fef2f2;border:1px solid #fca5a5;border-radius:8px;padding:12px 20px;min-width:140px;\">\n        <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#dc2626;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;\">Total Debits</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size:22px;font-weight:700;color:#b91c1c;\">$${total_debits.toFixed(2)}</div>\n      </div>\n      <div style=\"background:#f8fafc;border:1px solid #cbd5e1;border-radius:8px;padding:12px 20px;min-width:140px;\">\n        <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#475569;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;\">Confidence</div>\n        <div style=\"font-size:13px;color:#334155;margin-top:4px;\">\n          🟢 High: ${confidenceCounts.high} &nbsp;\n          🟡 Med: ${confidenceCounts.medium} &nbsp;\n          🔴 Low: ${confidenceCounts.low}\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <h3 style=\"color:#1e293b;margin-bottom:8px;\">Summary by GL Account</h3>\n    <table style=\"width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:14px;\">\n      <thead>\n        <tr style=\"background:#f1f5f9;\">\n          <th style=\"padding:8px 12px;text-align:left;border-bottom:2px solid #cbd5e1;\">Category</th>\n          <th style=\"padding:8px 12px;text-align:left;border-bottom:2px solid #cbd5e1;\">Account Code</th>\n          <th style=\"padding:8px 12px;text-align:left;border-bottom:2px solid #cbd5e1;\">Account Name</th>\n          <th style=\"padding:8px 12px;text-align:center;border-bottom:2px solid #cbd5e1;\">Transactions</th>\n          <th style=\"padding:8px 12px;text-align:right;border-bottom:2px solid #cbd5e1;\">Total Amount</th>\n        </tr>\n      </thead>\n      <tbody>${summaryRows}</tbody>\n    </table>\n  </div>\n` });\n\nreturn { status: \"success\" };",
      "definition_json": "{\"inputs\":[{\"name\":\"bank_statement\",\"type\":\"object\",\"description\":\"Source: {{bank_statement}} (columns: date, description, amount, type)\"},{\"name\":\"chart_of_accounts\",\"type\":\"object\",\"description\":\"Source: {{chart_of_accounts}} (columns: account_code, account_name, category)\"}],\"outputs\":[{\"name\":\"categorized_transactions\",\"type\":\"json_object\",\"description\":\"{ records: array of enriched transactions with GL assignment, summary: array of totals grouped by category, total_credits: number, total_debits: number }\"}]}",
      "chat_history": null,
      "created_at": "2026-04-11T05:33:25.451Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-11T05:33:58.873Z"
    },
    {
      "tool_id": "ctool-0a37ea",
      "name": "Categorization Report Builder",
      "description": "Receive categorized_transactions ({ records, summary, total_credits, total_debits }) and build a polished HTML report string. The report should have: (1) A header section with title 'Bank Statement — GL Categorization Report' and the run date. (2) A summary cards row showing Total Credits, Total Debits, and Net Amount. (3) A 'Summary by Category' table with columns: Category, Account Code, Account Name, Transactions, Total Amount — rows sorted by category name, with amounts formatted as currency. (4) A 'Transaction Detail' table with columns: Date, Description, Type, Amount, Account Code, Account Name, Category, Confidence — rows sorted by date, with credit rows styled green and debit rows styled red, and confidence badges (high=green, medium=orange, low=red). Use inline CSS for all styling. A clean, professional look with alternating row shading. Output the full HTML string as report_html.",
      "description_md": "## What it does\nReceive categorized_transactions ({ records, summary, total_credits, total_debits }) and build a polished HTML report string. The report should have: (1) A header section with title 'Bank Statement — GL Categorization Report' and the run date. (2) A summary cards row showing Total Credits, Total Debits, and Net Amount. (3) A 'Summary by Category' table with columns: Category, Account Code, Account Name, Transactions, Total Amount — rows sorted by category name, with amounts formatted as currency. (4) A 'Transaction Detail' table with columns: Date, Description, Type, Amount, Account Code, Account Name, Category, Confidence — rows sorted by date, with credit rows styled green and debit rows styled red, and confidence badges (high=green, medium=orange, low=red). Use inline CSS for all styling. A clean, professional look with alternating row shading. Output the full HTML string as report_html.\n\n## Inputs\n- **categorized_transactions** — {{categorized_transactions}}\n\n## Outputs\n- **report_html** — Complete self-contained HTML report string with inline CSS, summary cards, category summary table, and full transaction detail table.",
      "category": "custom_tool",
      "code": "const { records, summary, total_credits, total_debits } = api.getParameter(\"categorized_transactions\");\n\n// Helper: format currency\nfunction fmtCurrency(val) {\n  const n = Number(val) || 0;\n  return new Intl.NumberFormat('en-US', { style: 'currency', currency: 'USD' }).format(n);\n}\n\n// Helper: escape HTML\nfunction esc(str) {\n  if (str == null) return '';\n  return String(str).replace(/&/g,'&amp;').replace(/</g,'&lt;').replace(/>/g,'&gt;').replace(/\"/g,'&quot;');\n}\n\n// Run date\nconst runDate = new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' });\n\n// Net amount\nconst netAmount = (Number(total_credits) || 0) - (Number(total_debits) || 0);\n\n// Sort records by date\nconst sortedRecords = (records || []).slice().sort((a, b) => {\n  const da = new Date(a.date || a.Date || '');\n  const db = new Date(b.date || b.Date || '');\n  return da - db;\n});\n\n// Sort summary by category name\nconst sortedSummary = (summary || []).slice().sort((a, b) => {\n  const ca = String(a.category || a.Category || '');\n  const cb = String(b.category || b.Category || '');\n  return ca.localeCompare(cb);\n});\n\n// Build summary rows\nlet summaryRows = '';\nsortedSummary.forEach((row, i) => {\n  const bg = i % 2 === 0 ? '#ffffff' : '#f7f9fc';\n  const category = esc(row.category || row.Category || '');\n  const accountCode = esc(row.account_code || row.accountCode || row.AccountCode || '');\n  const accountName = esc(row.account_name || row.accountName || row.AccountName || '');\n  const transactions = row.transactions || row.Transactions || row.count || row.transaction_count || 0;\n  const totalAmount = Number(row.total_amount || row.totalAmount || row.TotalAmount || row.amount || 0);\n  summaryRows += `\n    <tr style=\"background:${bg};\">\n      <td style=\"padding:10px 14px;\">${category}</td>\n      <td style=\"padding:10px 14px;\">${accountCode}</td>\n      <td style=\"padding:10px 14px;\">${accountName}</td>\n      <td style=\"padding:10px 14px; text-align:center;\">${transactions}</td>\n      <td style=\"padding:10px 14px; text-align:right; font-weight:500;\">${fmtCurrency(totalAmount)}</td>\n    </tr>`;\n});\n\n// Build transaction detail rows\nlet detailRows = '';\nsortedRecords.forEach((row, i) => {\n  const bg = i % 2 === 0 ? '#ffffff' : '#f7f9fc';\n  const type = String(row.type || row.Type || row.transaction_type || '').toLowerCase();\n  const isCredit = type === 'credit';\n  const isDebit = type === 'debit';\n  const amountColor = isCredit ? '#1a7a4a' : isDebit ? '#c0392b' : '#333';\n  const amountBg = isCredit ? '#eafaf1' : isDebit ? '#fdf0ef' : 'transparent';\n\n  const confidence = String(row.confidence || row.Confidence || '').toLowerCase();\n  let badgeBg = '#aaa';\n  if (confidence === 'high') badgeBg = '#27ae60';\n  else if (confidence === 'medium') badgeBg = '#e67e22';\n  else if (confidence === 'low') badgeBg = '#e74c3c';\n\n  const date = esc(row.date || row.Date || '');\n  const description = esc(row.description || row.Description || '');\n  const typeDisplay = esc(row.type || row.Type || row.transaction_type || '');\n  const amount = Number(row.amount || row.Amount || 0);\n  const accountCode = esc(row.account_code || row.accountCode || row.AccountCode || '');\n  const accountName = esc(row.account_name || row.accountName || row.AccountName || '');\n  const category = esc(row.category || row.Category || '');\n\n  detailRows += `\n    <tr style=\"background:${bg};\">\n      <td style=\"padding:9px 12px;\">${date}</td>\n      <td style=\"padding:9px 12px; max-width:220px; overflow:hidden; text-overflow:ellipsis; white-space:nowrap;\">${description}</td>\n      <td style=\"padding:9px 12px; text-align:center;\">${typeDisplay}</td>\n      <td style=\"padding:9px 12px; text-align:right; color:${amountColor}; background:${amountBg}; font-weight:600;\">${fmtCurrency(amount)}</td>\n      <td style=\"padding:9px 12px;\">${accountCode}</td>\n      <td style=\"padding:9px 12px;\">${accountName}</td>\n      <td style=\"padding:9px 12px;\">${category}</td>\n      <td style=\"padding:9px 12px; text-align:center;\">\n        <span style=\"background:${badgeBg}; color:#fff; padding:3px 9px; border-radius:12px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600; text-transform:capitalize;\">${esc(confidence)}</span>\n      </td>\n    </tr>`;\n});\n\nconst html = `<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n<title>GL Categorization Report</title>\n<style>\n  * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }\n  body { font-family: 'Segoe UI', Arial, sans-serif; background: #f0f2f5; color: #333; padding: 30px; }\n  .container { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; }\n  .header { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a3c5e 0%, #2d6a9f 100%); color: #fff; padding: 30px 36px; border-radius: 10px 10px 0 0; }\n  .header h1 { font-size: 24px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.5px; }\n  .header p { margin-top: 6px; font-size: 13px; opacity: 0.85; }\n  .cards { display: flex; gap: 16px; padding: 20px 0; }\n  .card { flex: 1; background: #fff; border-radius: 8px; padding: 20px 24px; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.08); border-top: 4px solid #2d6a9f; }\n  .card.credits { border-top-color: #27ae60; }\n  .card.debits { border-top-color: #e74c3c; }\n  .card.net { border-top-color: #8e44ad; }\n  .card-label { font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1px; color: #888; font-weight: 600; }\n  .card-value { font-size: 26px; font-weight: 700; margin-top: 8px; }\n  .card.credits .card-value { color: #27ae60; }\n  .card.debits .card-value { color: #e74c3c; }\n  .card.net .card-value { color: #8e44ad; }\n  .section { background: #fff; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.07); margin-bottom: 24px; overflow: hidden; }\n  .section-title { background: #2d6a9f; color: #fff; padding: 13px 18px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.3px; }\n  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 13px; }\n  thead tr { background: #eaf1f8; }\n  thead th { padding: 11px 14px; text-align: left; font-weight: 700; color: #1a3c5e; border-bottom: 2px solid #c8daea; font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; }\n  tbody tr:hover { background: #eef4fb !important; }\n  .footer { text-align: center; color: #aaa; font-size: 12px; padding: 16px 0 4px; }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<div class=\"container\">\n  <div class=\"header\">\n    <h1>Bank Statement — GL Categorization Report</h1>\n    <p>Generated on ${esc(runDate)}</p>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"cards\">\n    <div class=\"card credits\">\n      <div class=\"card-label\">Total Credits</div>\n      <div class=\"card-value\">${fmtCurrency(total_credits)}</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"card debits\">\n      <div class=\"card-label\">Total Debits</div>\n      <div class=\"card-value\">${fmtCurrency(total_debits)}</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"card net\">\n      <div class=\"card-label\">Net Amount</div>\n      <div class=\"card-value\">${fmtCurrency(netAmount)}</div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"section\">\n    <div class=\"section-title\">Summary by Category</div>\n    <table>\n      <thead>\n        <tr>\n          <th>Category</th>\n          <th>Account Code</th>\n          <th>Account Name</th>\n          <th style=\"text-align:center;\">Transactions</th>\n          <th style=\"text-align:right;\">Total Amount</th>\n        </tr>\n      </thead>\n      <tbody>\n        ${summaryRows || '<tr><td colspan=\"5\" style=\"padding:16px; text-align:center; color:#aaa;\">No summary data available.</td></tr>'}\n      </tbody>\n    </table>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"section\">\n    <div class=\"section-title\">Transaction Detail</div>\n    <table>\n      <thead>\n        <tr>\n          <th>Date</th>\n          <th>Description</th>\n          <th style=\"text-align:center;\">Type</th>\n          <th style=\"text-align:right;\">Amount</th>\n          <th>Account Code</th>\n          <th>Account Name</th>\n          <th>Category</th>\n          <th style=\"text-align:center;\">Confidence</th>\n        </tr>\n      </thead>\n      <tbody>\n        ${detailRows || '<tr><td colspan=\"8\" style=\"padding:16px; text-align:center; color:#aaa;\">No transaction data available.</td></tr>'}\n      </tbody>\n    </table>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"footer\">GL Categorization Report &mdash; ${esc(runDate)}</div>\n</div>\n</body>\n</html>`;\n\napi.setParameter(\"report_html\", {\n  _meta: { type: \"text\", length: html.length },\n  data: html\n});\n\napi.addMessage({\n  markdown: `### ✅ GL Categorization Report Built\\n\\n- **Run Date:** ${runDate}\\n- **Total Credits:** ${fmtCurrency(total_credits)}\\n- **Total Debits:** ${fmtCurrency(total_debits)}\\n- **Net Amount:** ${fmtCurrency(netAmount)}\\n- **Categories:** ${sortedSummary.length}\\n- **Transactions:** ${sortedRecords.length}\\n\\nThe full HTML report has been saved to \\`report_html\\`.`\n});\n\nreturn { status: \"success\" };",
      "definition_json": "{\"inputs\":[{\"name\":\"categorized_transactions\",\"type\":\"object\",\"description\":\"Source: {{categorized_transactions}} (columns: records, summary, total_credits, total_debits)\"}],\"outputs\":[{\"name\":\"report_html\",\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"Complete self-contained HTML report string with inline CSS, summary cards, category summary table, and full transaction detail table.\"}]}",
      "chat_history": null,
